Class ConnectorInfoReportMojo

    @Mojo(name="connector-info",
      defaultPhase=SITE,
      requiresDependencyResolution=TEST,
      requiresReports=true,
      configurator="override")
public class ConnectorInfoReportMojo
extends org.apache.maven.reporting.AbstractMavenReport
    Goal generate a Connector Report.

    To debug execute this command: mvnDebug org.forgerock.maven.plugins:openicf-maven-plugin:connector-info

    Author:
    Laszlo Hordos

      • getOutputDirectory

        protected String getOutputDirectory()
        The output directory when the mojo is run directly from the command line. Implementors should use this method to return the value of a mojo parameter that the user may use to customize the output directory.
        Note: When the mojo is run as part of a site generation, Maven will set the effective output directory via MavenReport.setReportOutputDirectory(java.io.File) . In this case, the return value of this method is irrelevant. Therefore, developers should always call AbstractMavenReport.getReportOutputDirectory() to get the effective output directory for the report. The later method will eventually fallback to this method if the mojo is not run as part of a site generation.
        Specified by:
        getOutputDirectory in class org.apache.maven.reporting.AbstractMavenReport
        Returns:
        The path to the output directory as specified in the plugin configuration for this report.
